README: Generating GW Waveform and Flux Quantities
--------------------------------------------------
This calculator generates:
- r*h_plus
- r*h_cross
- kick velocity
- total energy radiated in gravitational waves
- total angular momentum radiated in gravitational waves

This version of the workflow has been simplified and organized by Cody Olson and Jamie Bamber.
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 1 — Ensure Psi4 Files Exist

The pipeline requires Psi4 data files.

If you only have Weyl4 data, first convert it using:
    format_Weyl4_data.py

This script reformats the Weyl4 output into the Psi4 format required by the waveform tools.
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 2 — Configure and Run the Waveform Script

Edit the script:
    make_GW_hlm_from_psi4.sh

You must set the following parameters:
- simulation name
- MADM (ADM mass)
- FFT cutoff frequency (omega)

Once configured, run the script. It will:
- process the Psi4 files
- run the Fortran waveform calculator
- generate waveform and analysis outputs

The primary outputs will include:
    rhphc.*.dat

One file is produced for each Psi4 extraction radius, along with additional analysis files.
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 3 — Copy Data for Visualization

Run:
    copy_wave_data.sh

This script moves the Psi4 files and rhphc.dat outputs into the `psi4_dir`
inside your `abid_bot` directory.

This allows the calculator to generate the corresponding `.vtk` files for visualization.
